      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) is the primary QoI, directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate device). Shear stress exposure time integral is the secondary QoI used to identify high-risk flow regions. Both QoIs are established in FDA guidance and peer-reviewed literature for CPB hemolysis assessment."
